deck: Mark Millar's and Sean Murphy's dynamic duo break the rules of time travel.
description:
The first Chrononauts series opens in Southeast Turkey, where Dr. Corbin Quinn is led to an ancient megalith housing an F-14 Tomcat fighter plane. Back in Texas, Corbin recounts the experience to his friend Dr. Danny Reilly. Corbin theorizes that the plane is one-in-the-same with a fighter plane that went missing in the 1970s. According to Quinn, the plane is just one of several time-displaced artifacts that has recently been discovered. Quinn invites Reilly to join his research team at the government-sponsored Chrono Division.

Several months later, Quinn and Reilly launch the satellite Mark Twain-One into the time stream, allowing television viewers to see the Battle of Gettysburg for the first time. Several months after that, Quinn and Reilly debut their time-travelling Chrono Suits, designed by Reilly himself. The suits allow the two to travel through time and run on batteries that last one hundred years time.

Before time launch, Corbin ruminates over the loss of his alcoholic father, whom he never made time for. He then calls his ex-wife Rachel and apologizes for never making time for her either. Danny kisses goodbye to his girlfriend Cindy and promises to be careful. Quinn enters the time stream first, but he is quickly knocked off course. He crash lands in Samarkand in 1504. Reilly follows Quinn into the time stream to rescue his friend.

Reilly emerges from the time stream in the middle of a battle between a Moghul army and a Samarkandian one. The Samarkandians, led by their general Sarvar, wield time-displaced weapons and drive time-displaced vehicles, giving them the edge over the Moghuls. After the battle, Reilly reveals his identity to the belligerent Sarvar. Recognizing Reilly’s name, Sarvar brings him to the capital of Samarkand.

Reilly learns that Quinn has become king of Samarkand and often upgrades his army with time-displaced equipment. While Reilly believes the two have been separated for forty minutes, Quinn reveals that he has been missing for four years. Quinn was able to return home at anytime but preferred not to because his life had fallen apart. Quinn shows Reilly that he’s been having fun across the time stream, even dating multiple famous women at once. Quinn invites Reilly to join him in adventuring through time, and Reilly accepts after disconnecting the tracking device in his Chrono-Suit. After witnessing the truth of the situation, Chrono Division sends a team of black ops agents led by Mannix to kill Quinn and Reilly before they completely destroy time. The team tracks the Chrononauts by tracing their batteries.

In 1920s New York, Gay Orlova, one of Quinn’s lovers and the girlfriend of mobster Lucky Luciano, discovers that Quinn has been cheating on her with other women. Gay decides to reveal the truth of her tryst to Lucky to get revenge on Quinn, even though she knows she will suffer just as much as he will.

Quinn and Reilly engage in numerous thrills across the time stream, including flying jets through the prehistoric era, meeting baby Jesus, and fighting in medieval wars, among other activities. They even take credit for numerous pop culture properties like Beatles songs, the Harry Potter series, and Breaking Bad. While touring with the band Morrissey, Reilly receives a telegram from himself stating that Quinn has been killed and that he himself has been fatally wounded. The telegram tells Reilly to show up in 1929 with a fast car to undo the predicament.

Lucky Luciano and his men ambush Quinn while he is in the shower. They burn his Chrono Suit, stranding him in the past. As Lucky is about to execute Quinn, Mannix’s Chrono Division team kills the mobsters. They let Quinn live until they can find Reilly. Quinn escapes from Mannix’s team and is rescued by Reilly in a 1970s De Tomaso Pantera.

Reilly and Quinn are pursued in a car chase through the time stream, passing through 1960s Miami, 1890s London, 200s Rome, 1940s Kursk, 1960s Dallas, and 200s B.C. China. In the 1450s Grand Canyon, one of Mannix’s soldiers falls to his death. Mannix and his team are stranded in a prehistoric period when a T-Rex smashes their vehicle. Mannix reveals that he survived the T-Rex attack, but is promptly stomped on. Arriving in 1504 Samarkand, the two decide to abandon Danny’s Chrono Suit to prevent Chrono Division from tracking them any further. They plan on starting a new life in 1504 London, but are captured by Sarvar, who now wears Reilly’s suit.

Sarvar’s men throw Quinn off a cliff and leave him to die in the desert, while they torture Reilly. Quinn embarks on a long journey around the world to the Grand Canyon, where he finds the corpse of one of Mannix’s men. Quinn uses the corpse’s Chrono Suit to amass an international, inter-time period army. Quinn leads his army in an assault on Samarkand, killing Sarvar with a jump jet.

Reilly convinces Quinn to fix the time stream after telling Quinn that he can still use the suit to be there for his loved ones whenever they needed him. Quinn’s personal life is repaired. When Quinn and Reilly complete their adventure, they discover that their activities still slightly altered the time stream, causing Reilly’s girlfriend Cindy to marry Mannix. The series ends in Reilly’s frustration.
name: Chrononauts

description:
Origin

The Northern Edge Guard are part of the existing standing forces which provide military defense, civil emergency response, and judicial policing for the magical creatures and magic-users of the two realms: Jade and the Retreat. The northern branch team has been featured in many issues due to close association with the Diggers family. The eastern branch was featured in the Edge Guard mini-series. The southern branch was finally featured in the color volume to show more unique characters in the current ongoing Infinity Engine story arc. It has been mentioned that the western branch is comprised of minotaurs but otherwise has not been featured.

Creation

The Northern Edge Guard was created by Gold Digger artist/writer/creator Fred Perry as an homage to the cartoon Thundercats and first appeared in Gold Digger #24.

Team Evolution

The northern branch of the Edge Guard is composed entirely of were-cats. Most of the original members have names which are anagrams for characters from the Thundercats. The team is seemingly specialized for investigation and pursuit as most of its members are skilled trackers or scouts. Its members mostly specialize in close quarters combat with very few equipped for ranged combat.

deck: Section Zero, a secret section of the UN, are a generational group of agents who are sent to explore reports of the uncanny and impossible.
description:
Creation

The comic title named Section Zero first appeared in the published works by both Gorilla Imprint and than Image Comics. He was created by Karl Kesel's and Tom Grummett's who also created the Section Zero concept. The concept behind the book is an Amalgam from Marvels Comics Fantastic Four and DC Comics the Silver Age Challengers of the Unknown.

Publication History

Section Zero was originally part of Image’s Gorilla Comics imprint back in 2000, alongside Kurt Busiek and Stuart Immonen’s Shockrockets, Mark Waid and Barry Kitson’s Empire, George Perez’s Crimson Plague, and Todd Dezago and Mike Wieringo’s Tellos. Lost civilizations, alien beings, strange creatures from beyond time and space are the subject matter which Tom Grummett and Karl Kesel’s developed the intentions behind the creator-owned comic.

Section Zero was originally proposed as an ongoing series, but due to financial problems experienced by the organizers of Gorilla Comics, only three issues were ultimately published; and then only after Image Comics stepped in to help out. A fourth issue was solicited, but was never published. Gorilla Comics was designed to be a creator owned company financed by a comics related website called eHero.com. The website proved to be a financial failure, leaving the creators to personally finance their own books. Along with the other Gorilla Comics creators, Kesel and Grummett attempted to continue the series they started, but these efforts proved to be unsuccessful.

History

The organization called Section Zero was created by the United Nations in the late 1940s to investigate unexplained phenomena around the world and to protect mankind from everything that "doesn’t" exist. The organization has has been in existence, albeit secretly, ever since. Over the many years that passed the charter has changed, members either aged, stepped down, died, or were replaced as time went on. However the group has changed the adventures continue whatever assigned task to investigate and, if necessary, fight the strange and unusual.

The original members of Section Zero, first operated during the 1950's and 1960's. These group of like minded explorers had to contend with "atomic power, giant insects, and little green men. The leader was Everest Pike, followed by the beautiful Sarina Ursari, the dapper Georges "Gorgeous" Seine, and Bernie Cork. These four faced the fantastic, and unknown and none of them had any special powers.

By the 1970s, the lineup of the team had changed. Everest Pike still lead the group, but he'd been joined by Tele Moteka, Sargasso the mer-monster, and Jesse Presley.

As the 1980s started the roster changed again, Tele Moteka was in charge of a team that consisted of Johnny Colossus, Artifax the mechanical man, and A.J. Keeler. Capturing the urban legend called the Jersey Devil on one of their outings. Tele would come to a tragic demise during this tenure.

Section Zero's latest members included Dr. Titania Challenger, the last living member of a family of scientific adventurers; Sam Wildman, the team's field leader and Doc Challenger's ex-husband; Tesla, a childlike alien who pilots the team's flying saucer. Tesla has no memory of his life before he began working for Section Zero; Thom Talesi, who went by the codename the 24-Hour Bug, an Asian-American teenager with a magical tattoo that allows him to transform into an insect-like being for a twenty-four hour period; Sargasso, a reptilian being who worked for Section Zero in the 1960's and 1970's only to be found in the present and A. J. Keeler, the group's leader. Keeler secretly also leads the Ghost Soldiers, a second covert group that may or may not be working against the best interests of Section Zero.
name: Section Zero

deck: A bio-synthetic slave race in the Gold Digger universe created by the Saurians to be living, psionic, personal computers.
description:
Amonians are a bio-synthetic slave race in the Gold Digger universe who resemble humans of average height and slender athletic build, but with salamander-like skin in varying colors. They were created along with Dragons by the Saurians, an ancient Earth race of hyper-intelligent dinosaurs. Where as the Dragons were variations of the dragon elder Exthilion created for manual labor, the Amonians were variations of their progenitor Amon designed to be living, psionic, personal computers.

Like Dragons and Saurians, Amonian minds could be copied into "environmental shells" - temporary bodies for use in environments too hazardous for their normal bodies.

At least one Amonian was used by the pseudo-Saurian Befadoc during his devastating raid on the Djinni realm of Yl'Dahjim. During the Amonian/Dragon rebellion against their Saurian creators, most of the Amonians were driven insane and wiped out by the psionic cry of the super-weapon Gigliathon .

In modern times, Gina Diggers and Ryan Tabbot confronted an active (but empty) Amonian environmental shell under the Egyptian pyramids. It has been shown that Ayane Anno is in fact one of the last Amonians in existence and that her servants Jarvis and Jeeves are Amonian environmental shells. It has also been shown that Theodore Diggers' mother Oracle was also an Amonian, making him and Gina Amonian/human hybrids.
name: Amonians

deck: The Amazon tribe of Jade realm is a humanoid race who are famous for their knowledge of genetic engineering and the reproductive arts in the Gold Digger universe.
description:
The Amazon race is one of the groups who moved to Jade realm at the end of the Age of Magic. They are descended from magically crafted "call girls" and "gigolos" created during Earth's Lost Age of Wonders by the Olympians (a subset of the Gardeners race). The tribe includes 2 subsets, the Athle and the Breeders.

Known regular Amazons

  • Casca, guardian of the Amazon library
  • Dalea, guardian of the Amazon library
  • Madame Xui, royal apothecary
  • Teala, captain in the royal Amazonian guard

The Athle include all the male Amazons and are all intensely handsome intellectuals and historians of the Amazon tribe. They are all under a minor psionic curse which makes they unable to perceive the intentions of others and so unable to grasp the concepts of deceit or mistrust. As a result, all female Amazons are intensely protective of the relatively few Athle. The Athle can only breed with Amazon females and always produce Athle children.

Known Athle

  • Elder Celestial
  • Fuchsia (also spelled Fushia)
  • Chroma

The Breeders represent the only female Amazons who are actually fertile and include the leaders of the tribe. They are particularly famous throughout Jade realm for their beauty, strength, being temperamental, and especially their knowledge of anatomy, genetic engineering, and the reproductive arts. Breeders can manipulate their own bodies to guarantee propagation of desired genetic traits in any children they have with members of other humanoid species. They were once noted as being able to breed with a were-cheetah male and produce were-cheetah children with 99% certainty. They are also trained in various chakras, pressure points, and similar arts to provide certain levels of pleasure, performance, and so on. As a result of Athle breeding, Amazon Breeders must seek out males from other humanoid species to continue the female side of the race.

deck: Amarans are an alien space-faring race in the Gold Digger universe. They resemble humanoid rabbits with purple fur.
description:
Amarans are a highly technical alien space-faring race. While they appear like humanoid rabbits with purple fur, they are cold-blooded and lay large clutches of eggs. On average, they are small (about 4.5 feet tall), lean, and not very strong or durable. They are vegetarians. Due to a long history as a prey species, they are very nervous and suspicious of others, almost to paranoia. Even after they become friends with someone, Amarans will be a bit uncertain if that person is a carnivore or omnivore. They also have a very high reproductive rate due to their prey history, but thanks to increasingly advanced defensive technology their families tend to be VERY large and extensive. Luckily they are quite sociable among themselves and one family branch will gladly help another branch with child-rearing.

During the reign of the Dynasty of the Stars, Amarans were treated as a sacrificial race and sent to the soul furnaces by the millions. Afterwards, the Amarans came to Earth a millennia ago in a city-ship as part of a joint colonization with Kryn and Atlantian city-ships. The Amaran ship was was severely damaged when it entered Earth's atmosphere and eventually crashed in the Antarctic. All of the Amarans onboard escaped and returned home except for 2, Jan and Rol. They survived using the hibernation pods until they awoke in the late 20th century.

Amaran technology is ultimately derived from Gardener and Dynasty Symbiots and includes:

  • phase units, wristbands that render the wearer intangible
  • work-bots equipped with various deadly weaponry and explosives
  • predator-predator suits, powerful sets of exoskeletal powered armor
name: Amarans

deck: Injected by alien technology, the Battleships are enhanced humans with superhuman speed, strength and invulnerability.
description:
During WWII, the Nazis had found alien technology with scripts, written in an alien language, describing how to use the technology to enhance humans. Feverishly trying to translate the scripts, the Nazis already started using the technology by experimenting on their prisoners of war. Only 1 in 5000 survived the injection with 'Wöden's Blood', a crystalline compound generated in a process somewhat analogous to fermentation. The injection created something called a disruption ball inside the human subject. Containing the unstable disruption ball is the most vital part of surviving the experiment. If not, the disruption ball could rip their body apart.

If contained, the ball gives the enhanced human superhuman speed, strength and invulnerability. The energy can also be used to destroy things. Some humans got the full potential of the powers. They were called Battleships. Others, with limited powers, were called Panzermensch.

However, using their powers would result in weakening their invulnerability.
name: Battleships
